Frequently asked questions.

What is an unlocked Pixel 9a?

An unlocked Pixel 9a is a phone that isnt tied to a specific operator. When you purchase an unlocked Pixel 9a, you get to choose which operator or plan works best for you.

Important: Pixel phones work with all major operators. But not all Pixel 4a (5G) and later phones have 5G functionality on all 5G networks. See a list of certified operators to make sure your phone works on its 5G network.

To use a SIM-unlocked phone:
1. Buy an unlocked Pixel phone from the Google Store.
2. Contact a mobile operator.
3. Follow their instructions to set up your phone with their service plan.

Is Pixel 9a dual SIM?

Pixel 9a has dual SIM functionality. You can use 2 SIMs: 1 physical SIM card and 1 eSIM. You can choose which SIM to use for which action, like messaging or calling. This option is called Dual SIM Dual Standby (DSDS). On the Pixel 9a if your operator allows, you can use two eSim profiles simultaneously and connect to two 5G networks in dual SIM mode at the same time.

Does Pixel 9a have 5G network compatibility?

Yes, Pixel 9a works with 5G networks. The type of 5G service depends on both the phone model and the operator network. Learn more about 5G.

What is included in the Pixel 9a box?

Your Pixel 9a purchase comes with a 1 m USB-C to USB-C cable (USB 2.0) and SIM tool. Pixel 9a does not come with a 45W USB-C Power Charger, but that can be purchased separately.

How does the Google Store exchange programme work?

Our exchange programme with Cashify makes it easy to get the latest Google Pixel phones. You can exchange Google Pixel phones and phones from most other manufacturers. How much you will get for your exchange depends on the model, manufacturer, and condition of your phone. If your old device is eligible, youll receive a refund via Netbanking or UPI once Cashify inspects your old device.

When you order a new Pixel, youll get an estimate for your old device. After your new Pixel device arrives, you will be notified to set up an exchange appointment with Cashify. A Cashify representative will then collect your old device and send payment after inspection during the appointment (the amount may be adjusted). Learn more about the Google Store exchange programme.

How do I switch from an Android phone or an iPhone to Pixel 9a?

Switching to Pixel is easy. You can transfer your stuff, like photos or messages, from your old phone to your Pixel in a few simple steps. Learn more about switching to Pixel.

Where can I find setup instructions and tips for my new Pixel 9a?

Move your stuff over, personalise your settings and explore Pixel features to get the most out of your phone. Get more help 24/7 at g.co/pixel/support.

Who should I contact if I have questions about my Pixel 9a purchase?

Visit our Help Centre to contact us and get help.

Where can I find the manufacturer, importer, and country of origin details?

Information with respect to the product including manufacturer, importer, country of origin, and other related information can be found on the Product Legal Declarations page.
